abstract: Talks to reunite Cyprus after decades of division break down with two sides no closer to compromise and no date set for new round; Greek Cypriot leader Nicos Anastasiades and Turkish Cypriot leader Mustafa Akinci each blame other for impasse.

headline.print_headline: Cyprus Talks Break Down, and 2 Sides Trade Blame
headline.main: Cyprus Peace Talks End With Each Side Blaming the Other

snippet: Negotiations to end a decades-old division between Greek and Turkish Cypriots broke down Tuesday, and no date was set for a new round of talks....
lead_paragraph: Negotiations to end a decades-old division between Greek and Turkish Cypriots broke down Tuesday, and no date was set for a new round of talks.
